eventFwdTableModificationStatus.name: eventFwdTableModificationStatus
eventFwdTableModificationStatus.description: Indicates the combination of possible functions allowed on the lmsEventFwdTable table, subject to overriding SNMP security attributes and the ACCESS clause restrictions on the objects themselves. The values are: unknown - Managers privileges are unknown. no-access - Managers may neither read nor write to this table. read-only - Managers may only read the table, they cannot add or delete conceptual rows and cannot change the value of any variable, even those with ACCESS of 'read-write'. read-modify - Managers may read the table, and change the value of variables whose ACCESS is 'read-write'. read-create - Managers may read the table, change the value of variables whose ACCESS is 'read-write', and create or delete conceptual rows in the table.

nextFwdEntryIndex.name: nextFwdEntryIndex
nextFwdEntryIndex.description: The index that may be used by a manager on a 'set-request' PDU to create a new conceptual row in the lmsEventFwdTable table.

trapWindowTime.name: trapWindowTime
trapWindowTime.description: A control time window, expresses in 1/100ths of a second, used in conjunction with the maxTrapsPerWindow variable to prevent a 'trap storm' caused by a rapidly recurring error condition .

maxTrapsPerWindow.name: maxTrapsPerWindow
maxTrapsPerWindow.description: The maximum number of traps to be forwarded in the time interval expressed in the trapWindowTime variable. Used to prevent a 'trap storm' caused by a rapidly recurring error condition.

numDroppedMaxPerWindowTraps.name: numDroppedMaxPerWindowTraps
numDroppedMaxPerWindowTraps.description: The number of traps intended for this destination, which were not forwarded due to the maxTrapsPerWindow count being met or exceeded.

lmsEventFwdTable.name: lmsEventFwdTable
lmsEventFwdTable.description: The table holding information to control/administer forwarding of LMS events to SNMP-based management stations or applications.

lmsEventFwdEntry.name: lmsEventFwdEntry
lmsEventFwdEntry.description: The entry associated with each destination to which LMS events should be forwarded as SNMP traps.

fwdEntryIndex.name: fwdEntryIndex
fwdEntryIndex.description: The integer index into the lmsEventFwdTable table.

rowStatus.name: rowStatus
rowStatus.description: The status of the conceptual row. These are mapped to the same values as the RowStatus textual conversion in SNMPv2 and carry the same semantics.

destinationNetAddr.name: destinationNetAddr
destinationNetAddr.description: The network address of the destination entity for trap forwarding.

destinationCommunity.name: destinationCommunity
destinationCommunity.description: The community name to be used when sending traps to the destination entity. This variable is non-defined in SNMPv2 implementions.

destinationPort.name: destinationPort
destinationPort.description: The UDP port at the 'destinationNetAddr' to which the trap should be sent.

forwardingEnabled.name: forwardingEnabled
forwardingEnabled.description: Indicates whether forwarding is enabled for this destination at the present time. Used to temporarily suspend forwarding.

forwardingFilterName.name: forwardingFilterName
forwardingFilterName.description: Undefined at the present time - bge.

lastTrapSequenceNumber.name: lastTrapSequenceNumber
lastTrapSequenceNumber.description: The sequence number of the last trap sent to this destination. All traps sent to a given destination are sequenced via a 32-bit, wrapping counter. A manager may use this variable to determine if any traps for this destination have been 'lost'.

lastTrapTime.name: lastTrapTime
lastTrapTime.description: The value of sysUpTime as included in the last trap sent to this destination.

numDroppedDisabledTraps.name: numDroppedDisabledTraps
numDroppedDisabledTraps.description: The number of traps intended for this destination, which were not forwarded due to the variable forwardingEnabled begin set to disabled(2).

lmsEvComponentType.name: lmsEvComponentType
lmsEvComponentType.description: Identifies the type of LMS component issuing the event.

lmsEvComponentDN.name: lmsEvComponentDN
lmsEvComponentDN.description: Identifies the most unique (rightmost) portion of the Spyder Distinguished Name of the component issuing the event. The combination of lmsEvComponentType and lmsEvComponentDN MUST uniquely identify the issuing component.

lmsEvDbId.name: lmsEvDbId
lmsEvDbId.description: Identifies the unique key used to identify this event in the LMS event database.

lmsEvOID.name: lmsEvOID
lmsEvOID.description: Identifies the specific LMS event OID conatined in the LMS event.

numLmsEvSequences.name: numLmsEvSequences
numLmsEvSequences.description: A monotonically increasing, wrapping counter indication the sequence number of this event, relative to the destination of the trap. Events that are not forwarded to a destination (destination temporarily disabled, windowTime exceeded) do not cause this sequence number to increase.

lmsEvSeverity.name: lmsEvSeverity
lmsEvSeverity.description: The original severity assigned to the LMS event.

lmsEvSupportingText.name: lmsEvSupportingText
lmsEvSupportingText.description: Textual information supporting the event data. The meaning of the brief text must be obvious in the context of the trap - for the sake of brevity it need not be a gramatically correct sentence.

lmsCritical.name: lmsCritical
lmsCritical.description: A critical alarm forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.

lmsMajor.name: lmsMajor
lmsMajor.description: A major alarm forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.

lmsMinor.name: lmsMinor
lmsMinor.description: A minor alarm forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.

lmsWarning.name: lmsWarning
lmsWarning.description: A warning or indeterminate forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.

lmsCleared.name: lmsCleared
lmsCleared.description: A cleared forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.

lmsInformational.name: lmsInformational
lmsInformational.description: An informational event forwarded from the LMS event subsystem.
